Class Difference

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mslab.core.Difference
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class Difference
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Externalizable, java.lang.Cloneable
    This class represents a difference, that is a ByteArray.

        public Difference(int[] delta,
          int position)
        Creates a new difference, treats all items in the given items as bytes of a difference. The given values are placed in positions position.. position + delta.length; the first position bytes are filled up with zeroes.
